Name: Kara Kuzhambu
Tamil Name: கார குழம்பு
Category: curry
Sub Category: kuzhambu
Diet: vegetarian, vegan
Difficulty: medium
Prep Time: 15 minutes
Cook Time: 15 minutes
Servings: 6
Description:
Kara Kuzhambu is a spicy and tangy Tamil Nadu style tamarind gravy made with drumstick and brinjal. It features a rich masala paste with coconut, spices, and sambar powder that adds depth and flavour. This comforting kuzhambu is a favourite in Chettinad and Tamil homes and pairs perfectly with steamed rice.

Ingredients:

* Sesame oil (நல்லெண்ணெய் - நல்லெண்ணெய்): 1 tsp (for masala) + 3 tbsp (for cooking)
* Fenugreek seeds (வெந்தயம் - வெந்தயம்): ¼ tsp
* Coriander seeds (தனியா - தனியா): 2 tsp
* Fennel seeds (சோம்பு - சோம்பு): 1 tsp
* Dried red chillies (காய்ந்த மிளகாய் - காய்ந்த மிளகாய்): 2
* Grated coconut (தேங்காய் துருவல் - தேங்காய் துருவல்): ¼ cup
* Sambar powder (சாம்பார் பொடி - சாம்பார் பொடி): 2 tsp
* Salt (உப்பு - உப்பு): ½ tsp (for paste) + ½ tsp (for gravy)
* Mustard seeds (கடுகு - கடுகு): ¼ tsp
* Curry leaves (கறிவேப்பிலை - கறிவேப்பிலை): 2 sprigs
* Onion (வெங்காயம் - வெங்காயம்): 1 (medium, chopped)
* Tomato (தக்காளி - தக்காளி): 1 (ripe, chopped)
* Brinjal (கத்தரிக்காய் - கத்தரிக்காய்): 5 (chopped)
* Drumstick (முருங்கைக்காய் - முருங்கைக்காய்): 1 (chopped)
* Tamarind paste (புளி பேஸ்ட் - புளி பேஸ்ட்): 2-3 tbsp (or small lime sized tamarind)
* Jaggery (வெல்லம் - வெல்லம்): 1 tsp
* Water (தண்ணீர் - தண்ணீர்): as needed

Steps:

1. Heat 1 tsp sesame oil in a pan. Add fenugreek seeds, coriander seeds, fennel seeds, and dried red chillies. Fry until aromatic.
2. Add grated coconut and fry for a couple of minutes. Switch off the flame.
3. Add sambar powder and ½ tsp salt. Mix well and let it cool.
4. Grind the cooled mixture with ½ cup water into a smooth paste. Set aside.
5. Heat 3 tbsp sesame oil in a pressure cooker or pan. Add mustard seeds and curry leaves. Let them splutter.
6. Add chopped onion and sauté until soft. Add chopped tomato and cook until juicy.
7. Add chopped drumstick and brinjal. Add ½ cup water, ground masala paste, tamarind paste, remaining salt, and jaggery.
8. Mix gently, cover and pressure cook for 2 whistles (or simmer on low flame for 15 minutes if not using cooker).
9. Once pressure releases, open and check consistency. Add hot water if needed to get a pouring consistency.
10. Mix well and serve hot.

Tips:

* Use generous sesame oil for authentic taste and to prevent bitterness from fenugreek.
* Do not over-roast fenugreek seeds as they can make the gravy bitter.
* Adjust water after cooking to get the right gravy consistency.
* This kuzhambu tastes better the next day as flavours develop.

Variations:
Drumstick only kara kuzhambu, Brinjal kara kuzhambu, Mixed vegetable kara kuzhambu

Commonly served with:
Steamed rice, Appalam, Poriyal

